# Copy this file to ".env" in the same folder as main.js and fill in values.
# Never commit .env (it is gitignored). If a secret was ever pasted in chat or
# committed, revoke it in Notion and create a new integration secret.
#
# OAuth "public integration" client ID/secret are not used by this app — use an
# internal integration secret as NOTION_TOKEN below.
#
# NOTION_TOKEN: https://www.notion.so/my-integrations → your integration →
#   "Internal Integration Secret" (starts with secret_). Share the target
#   database with this integration (⋯ on the database page → Connect to → your integration).
#
# Packaged app (.exe): put .env in the app user data folder, e.g.
#   %APPDATA%\recruit-my-english\.env
# On first run the installer copies this template there. You only need NOTION_TOKEN
# in AppData `.env`; NOTION_DATABASE_ID is taken from the app bundle (below) so each
# new build uses the DB you baked in — not an old seeded copy from a previous install.
# To point the installed app at a different DB instead, put NOTION_SKIP_BUNDLED_DATABASE_ID=1
# in `%APPDATA%\recruit-my-english\.env` and set NOTION_DATABASE_ID there.
#
# NOTION_DATABASE_ID: Open your database as a full page. Copy the ID from the URL path:
#   https://www.notion.so/workspace/352b1f14cd6a80f797aff1658ee608bc?v=...
#   Use this path segment — not the ?v=... value (that is a view id). 32 hex chars; hyphens optional.
#   Use the 32-character ID (with or without hyphens). The app resolves the
#   data source from this id (changing this switches databases).
#
# Teacher pay slip PDFs: match the teacher's Supabase sign-in email. Use a column named
# "Email", "Teacher email", "E-mail", etc., or put the address in any property on the row
# (title, rich text, email field, formula text). @googlemail.com and @gmail.com are treated as the same.
# Large databases: the app follows Notion pagination (100 rows per request, up to
# the API limit of about 10,000 rows per data source).
#
# Per-teacher Notion databases (admin + teacher views): run supabase/migrations/004_teacher_notion.sql
# in the Supabase SQL editor, then set public.teachers.notion_database_id (and optionally
# notion_data_source_id) per teacher. When at least one teacher has these set, the admin
# home loads one tab per teacher. If no teacher has a link, the app falls back to
# NOTION_DATABASE_ID / NOTION_DATA_SOURCE_ID above (shared database + email matching).
# The same internal integration must be invited to every teacher database.
#
# NOTION_DATA_SOURCE_ID (optional): Only if GET /v1/databases returns no data_sources
# (e.g. some wiki setups). Omit when possible — a stale value can point at the wrong DB.
# NOTION_DATA_SOURCE_ID=

NOTION_TOKEN=
NOTION_DATABASE_ID=

# Sign-in uses Supabase Auth (email + password in the app). Enable the Email
# provider under Authentication → Providers. For quick local testing, turn off
# "Confirm email" on that Email provider screen so new users can sign in
# immediately without opening an inbox link. The authorized admin email is set in
# auth-store.js (ALLOWED_ADMIN_EMAIL), not in .env.
#
# In Project Settings → API, set SUPABASE_URL to the project URL and
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY to the anon / public client key (legacy JWT starting with
# eyJ… or a publishable key if your project uses that — same field the JS client expects).
# Use these exact names (not NEXT_PUBLIC_* — that is for Next.js only).
# Leave blank here; put real values only in your private .env (not committed).
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
#
# If the app reports that public.teachers is missing: open Supabase Dashboard →
# SQL, paste and run supabase/migrations/001_teachers.sql for this project.
# For teacher profile fields and avatar uploads, also run 002_teacher_profile.sql.
# For the admin Teachers tab (list everyone), run 003_admin_teacher_directory.sql
# and insert your admin email into public.app_admins (same as auth-store.js).

# If Notion returns 401 "API token is invalid": the secret may have been
# refreshed, or you pasted the wrong value. Use only the integration's
# "Internal Integration Secret" from my-integrations — not an OAuth client secret.
